The paper focuses on person retrieval using convolutional neural networks and part-level features. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The paper also proposes a refined part pooling method and a strong convolutional baseline, which involves learning discriminative features, indicating that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper involves image content consistency and feature extraction, which may fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories.
